         <abstract>
            <p>This paper presents a class of new second-order accurate $(2K + 3)$-point explicit schemes for the computation of weak solutions of hyperbolic conservation laws, that are total-variation-diminishing under a CFL restriction of $K$. These highly nonlinear schemes are obtained by applying a nonoscillatory first-order accurate $(2K + 1)$-point scheme to a modified flux. The so-derived second-order accurate schemes achieve high resolution, while retaining the robustness of the original first-order accurate scheme.</p>
          </abstract>
